24/08/2006
PANCEVO, Serbia -- US Ambassador to Belgrade Michael Polt delivered over $1.2m worth of equipment for public protection purposes Wednesday, donated by the US armed forces' European Command. Defence Minister Zoran Stankovic said that it would be used to establish four protection centres in Belgrade, Novi Sad, Kragujevac and Nis. He also described the military co-operation between Serbia and the United States as developing, with a bilateral agreement expected to be signed next month. (Danas - 24/08/06; Tanjug - 23/08/06)
